        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 5:58PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 558 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Yoder, or 34 miles east of Colorado Springs, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Yoder and Rush.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
